layers.name: Case-by-Case
layers.description: Partial state and province coverage of the Pacific Northwest. Geographic area covers southern BC and Alberta; Washington, Oregon and Idaho; northern California, Nevada, and Utah; western Montana and Wyoming. Pacific Coastline from northern California to Queen Charlotte Islands, B.C. including all of Vancouver Island B.C.
